Review Title: Friendly and helpful staff. Delicious food. Cozy atmosphere.
Review Text: Its such a wonderful evening that we had at Pasley. We ordered 4 dishes and all of them were good. The chef himself came to our table and listened to our opinion. The staff were extremely helpful, they give us 2 beverages for free. Highly recommended!!!

Everything was good, including the price considering their city central location. The reason I didn't give them 5 star because their ice cream was made somewhat sloppy so a piece of ice cream felt down to the cup rim
great restaurant!  if you are nearby, be sure to stop by for a meal!  super! thanks to the staff for the excellent and fast service🥳👏👏👏

Giá trị: 5
Dịch vụ: 5
Đồ ăn: 5
Review Text: We dined here twice, on the 8th and 14th of March. The first time was International Womens day and the staff wrote a card for my wife. The second time we were the only diners. We had three of their signature dishes being the "I wanna cry shrimp", grilled squid salad and the thoroughly satisfying "one bite pork noodle bundles" on our first trip; and on the second we opted for grilled beef rolls in piper leaves, and the northern light spicy grilled squid, which was spicy. The staff took their time to ask about any allergies and level of spice. hopefully they will reopen soon. There were three restaurants in this building, and this one is on level 5, you enter through the ground floor one and up a lift.

Review Title: Delightful place to enjoy our last dinner in Vietnam!
Review Text: located in a good / vibey area. We were there on March 15 - during the COVID 19 outbreak. We were the last guests on the last day of business before lockdown.  This did not detract from our experience at all.  We were welcomed by all with friendly smiles and comments. The Staff were just great, helpful with menu suggestions and attentive.  The meals chosen suited our different tastes and were really tasty, well presented and great. we enjoyed superb coconut cream coffee - must be tried! We were given a beautiful handmade "thank you" card when we left.  All round really worth the visit.  They are difficult to find. - at 130 Nguyen Trai (street), only have a SMALL sign outside the  restaurant below on street level. Enter the ground floor restaurant and tell them you want to go to the 5th floor. and there you'll find your host waiting for the lift door to open and to welcome you. support them when the lock down is lifted - - they're just great!

Review Title: Average taste. Where are all the spices?
Review Text: Staff is very friendly and helpful. Food looks very pretty on the plate. But the taste is average, nothing special. My beef was chewy. To call a restaurant “house of spices”  there should be more spice options and dips and... on the menus. Prices where ok.

We had a lovely meal, the staff were very friendly and helpful with suggestions of what to order according to our tolerance level of spice!  There was a charming young man who wrote us a list of places he recommended and also some Vietnamese phrases, and he gave us a card for International Women’s Day!
Thức ăn ngon, trang trí đẹp. Nhân viên thân thiện. Rất khuyến khích tôi muốn khóc tôm và cá mekong. Cuốn sách tốt hơn trước.

Review Title: Bữa ăn đầu tiên của chúng tôi tại thành phố Hồ Chí Minh
Review Text:
Chúng tôi cam ở đây abt 1 w trước. Vị trí của họ là trên
 Tầng 5 nên chúng tôi đi qua một nhà hàng khác. Vô cùng đói khát và không thể chờ đợi lâu hơn nữa, chúng tôi đã yêu cầu 1 starer chia sẻ và 2 nguồn chính cho mỗi cái. Tin tôi đi món salad mực nướng thật tuyệt vời. Tôi có thể cảm thấy vị chua, ngọt, một chút cay trong món ăn đó. Con mực rất tươi như thể chúng vừa đánh bắt từ biển. Không chỉ là stater ngon mà còn có 2 món chính là tuyệt vời. Tôi đã thử món cá sông mekong và con gái tôi đã nướng tôm với sốt tiêu đen. Con cá hoàn toàn không xương. Tôi đã rất ấn tượng bởi mùi sả chiên giòn. Cá philê bên ngoài giòn và bên trong ngon ngọt. Để tôm, họ ướp với nước sốt tự làm. Nó có thể bao gồm tỏi, hạt tiêu đen và một ít bột mì. Nước sốt đặc quánh như sữa đặc. Thưởng thức với cơm trắng nóng là sự kết hợp hoàn hảo. OMG tôi không yêu cầu thêm. Các mocktails là tuyệt vời, tôi đã nghiện. Sau khi chúng tôi kết thúc, người quản lý đã cho chúng tôi một số địa điểm để đến Sài Gòn, giúp chúng tôi o đối xử với bạn, khiến bạn cảm thấy như đang ở nhà. Cảm ơn bạn đã chào đón nồng nhiệt. Tôi chắc chắn sẽ giới thiệu cho bạn bè nếu họ đến thăm Sài Gòn.

Review Title: The best dinner of my time in Vietnam
Review Text:
Really - dinner there last night was the culinary highlight of my ten days in Vietnam, a country with one of the most delicate and interesting cuisines in the world. As a starter, I had the most delicious prawns with a fiery dipping sauce, but not so fiery that it blew away the sweetness and freshness of the seafood.
For my main course, I had difficulty choosing, but eventually decided on river fish with a green chilli sauce.  It looked quite beautiful, but greed overcame everything and I forgot to take a photograph. The fish was perfectly cooked, and came with a salad of green mango and carrot, rice and spiced corn. So far, so fabulous. But then there was the green chilli sauce, a perfect balance of sweet, sour and heat. Amazing! I'm not sitting on the fence here. I loved this restaurant.

We booked and turned up around 7.30 to find a tiny, virtually empty restaurant.  I’ve no idea why this place wasn’t bombed out because the staff were warm and friendly, extremely helpful when it came to ordering and very attentive throughout.  Our table was adequate and comfortable.  The simple menu is great, offering very well prepared, delicious local food in large portions for little cost.  We shared two starters, I wanna cry shrimp, hot and spicy, and chicken wings, sweet and sticky. We followed by sharing a delicious fried Black Pomfret fish.  The cocktails were similarly great and cheap so we had several.  Absolutely lovely evening out.  Can’t recommend this place more highly - 10 out of 10.

Mysigt ställe, toppenservice och god mat. Supertrevlig servitör som presenterade alla rätter på ett förtroendeingivande sätt. En extra bonus till servitören som skrev ned sina restips till staden för oss samt lite användbara fraser!

Review Text: We really love this place especially the staff. They are friendly, enthusiastic and professional. They provided us the best service they got with their passion. Review Text: Wandering around looking a great place for the local food we found this restaurant on TripAdvisor. With its good reviews we decided to go to the fifth floor of the building to try food even though there is another restaurant downstairs. Everything in this place was good. It's a small venue with nice decorations. The food was well prepared and delicious.  I got the beef rolls in the piper leaf which was really tasty. The waitress taught me how to eat it by using their noodles bundle to roll every and deep in the homemade fishsauce. Just like the way to eat Vietnamese pancakes, using some herbs to make the flavour stronger. When we finished our meal, the waiter came and gave us some recommendations and tips in Saigon. What a nice experience!

Firstly, you enter this restaurant through another restaurant and take the lift to the fifth floor
The food is excellent with a great selection and fabulous quality and presentation
We had prawns and beef and the tastes were sublime accompanied by a passion fruit mojito and a bottle of red wine
Best of all was the service. We were looked after by Chilli who have us advice on what to order. On leaving he gave us a list of places to visit and a good luck message.
A great start to our visit to HC M city
Ottimo ristorante. Personale molto cortese. Presentazione dei piatti curata. Ci hanno anche dato consigli su cosa vedere in città

Review Title: Lovely restaurant, good food and very kind staff
Review Text:
I loved this place, food was spicy and good, served in a very nice and clean way.
Staff has been so cheerful, nice and helpful giving us advices about our stay in Vietnam.

Review Text:
A great dinner for our wedding anniversary. The place was extremely clean and beautiful. We sat next to the glass and the view was amazing!
The waiter (Long) came to explain the menu and he asked about our allergies. My partner couldn't eat nuts and they kindly separate peanuts on the side for me so that we could share the dishes. We had three courses which was fit for two and the price was cheap as the portion was big.
I had a passionfruit mojito and it was great. Thank you for such a lovely evening!
